[4] United Arab Emirates - food safety
Date: Wed 10 Nov 2010
Source: Emirates 24/7 News [edited]
<http://www.emirates247.com/news/emirates/dm-launches-safe-sacrifice-campaign-for-eid-2010-11-10-1.316029>


Dubai Municipality has launched an awareness campaign called "Ensure your
health by safe sacrifice" in order to protect public health in preparation
for Eid Al Adha.

The campaign aims to introduce ways of safe sacrificial slaughter, create
public awareness of the importance of the role of the veterinary doctor,
the dangers of slaughtering outside, and seeking the services of roaming
butchers. The campaign targets housewives, school and university students
and all members of the society.

The campaign kicked off on Sunday [7 Nov 2010] in schools and an exhibition
on the ways of safe slaughter and warning of the dangers of slaughtering
outside on the public health was held in the main building of Dubai
Municipality on Wednesday [10 Nov 2010].

The municipality has assigned a number of employees of the Public Health
Services Department to educate people in the cattle market. Awareness
leaflets and booklets will also be distributed through cooperative
societies, vegetable markets, cattle markets, Auto Market, and the
municipality centres on the benefits of safe slaughter and the risks of
slaughtering outside.

In addition to this, the municipality will organise awareness lectures at
schools, universities and Princess Haya centres. At the municipality level,
employees will be educated through a series of awareness messages by
sending emails. The municipality will also coordinate with the Department
of Islamic Affairs and Charitable Activities in Dubai to raise awareness
about this subject through the Friday sermons.

