[5] Saudi Arabia - food safety
Date: Wed 10 Nov 2010
Source: Arab News [edited]
<http://arabnews.com/saudiarabia/article185749.ece>


Five slaughterhouses and livestock markets for Eid Al-Adha have been
approved by the Jeddah municipality.

The 8 approved livestock markets are situated close to Al-Shamali,
Al-Sabeel and Hira slaughterhouses, as well as the Central Cattle Souk. The
approved abattoirs are the Main Jeddah Slaughterhouse and the ones at
Al-Nuzha, Hira, Al-Sabeel, and the Cattle Souk.

The municipality advised customers who buy lambs from mobile salesmen to
demand an invoice for proof of purchase and contact information. The
municipality has also warned the public against the use of illegal or
unlicensed slaughterhouses.

The municipality has also marked the locations where traders can sell in
pickup vans and urged those who want to slaughter their own animals to
abide by hygienic regulations, including a veterinary examination of the
animal.

[byline: Dr Yasmin Akram]

